## üü¢ Introduction to HTML

- What is HTML?
- How the web works (HTML + CSS + JS)
- HTML document structure (`<!DOCTYPE html>`, `<html>`, `<head>`, `<body>`)
- Setting up an HTML file

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title>My First Page</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Hello World</h1>
  </body>
</html>
```
````

---

## üß± Basic HTML Elements

### Text Elements

- `<h1>` to `<h6>` ‚Äì Headings
- `<p>` ‚Äì Paragraph
- `<br>`, `<hr>`
- `<strong>`, `<em>`, `<mark>`, `<small>`

### Lists

- `<ul>`, `<ol>`, `<li>`
- `<dl>`, `<dt>`, `<dd>`

### Links & Media

- `<a href="">`
- `<img src="" alt="">`
- `<video>`, `<audio>`, `<iframe>`

### Forms

- `<form>`, `<input>`, `<textarea>`, `<button>`
- `<select>`, `<option>`, `<label>`, `name`, `value`, `placeholder`, `required`

### Tables

- `<table>`, `<tr>`, `<td>`, `<th>`, `<thead>`, `<tbody>`

---

## üü° Intermediate HTML Concepts

### Semantic HTML

- `<header>`, `<footer>`, `<nav>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<aside>`, `<main>`

### Form Enhancements

- `type="email"`, `type="number"`, `type="date"`
- Form validation attributes: `required`, `pattern`, `min`, `max`, `readonly`

### Meta Tags

- `<meta charset="UTF-8">`
- `<meta name="viewport">`
- `<meta name="description">`

### Favicons

- `<link rel="icon" href="favicon.ico">`

### HTML Entities

- `&copy;`, `&amp;`, `&lt;`, `&gt;`, `&nbsp;`

---

## üîµ Advanced HTML Features

### Embedded Content

- `<iframe>` for videos/maps
- `<embed>` and `<object>`

### Data Attributes

```html
<button data-user-id="42">Click Me</button>
```

### SVG & Canvas

- `<svg>`, `<circle>`, `<path>`
- `<canvas>` for drawing with JS

### Web Storage

- `localStorage`, `sessionStorage` via JS

### Custom Elements (Web Components)

- `<my-component></my-component>`

---

## üß† SEO, Accessibility & Best Practices

### SEO (Search Engine Optimization)

- Use semantic tags properly
- Proper heading hierarchy
- Meta descriptions
- Alt text for images

### Accessibility (a11y)

- `alt`, `aria-label`, `aria-hidden`
- Keyboard navigation support
- Use landmarks: `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<footer>`

### Best Practices

- Keep HTML structure clean and nested
- Use comments: `<!-- This is a comment -->`
- Don‚Äôt skip heading levels
- Avoid inline styles

